    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#cdl-gwaider1997"/>, n. <citedRange>5</citedRange>, pl. II.b-c</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>47.2176</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#GVCyr"/> <citedRange>006</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#chamoux2001"/>, pp. <citedRange>1308-1310</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>51.2207</citedRange></bibl>.
                   </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                    <div type="textpart" subtype="text">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><name type="animal" nymRef="#Τύραννος">Τύραννος</name> <w lemma="κύων">κύων</w>
                    </ab>
                    </div> 
                
                   <div type="textpart" subtype="verse">
                       <lg>
                           <l met="dactylic heptameter" real="+--|++|+--|++|+--|+--|++">
                        <lb n="2"/><w lemma="ἐνθάδε">Ἐνθάδε</w> δὴ <w lemma="κεῖμαι">κεῖμαι</w>
                        <lb n="3"/><w lemma="ὑπό"><unclear>ὑπ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ὸ</supplied></w> <w lemma="γαῖα">γ<unclear>αί</unclear>ης</w>, <w lemma="δεσπότης">δέσπο<lb n="4" break="no"/>τ<unclear>α</unclear></w>, <w lemma="πολύς">πολλὰ</w> <w lemma="πονέω">πονή<lb n="5" break="no"/>σας</w></l>
                       </lg>
                   </div>
               
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>     
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
                <p>Le chien Tyrannos.</p>
                <p>Ici je gis sous la terre, mon maître, après bien des fatigues.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
                <p>The dog Tyrannos.</p>
                <p>Here I lay under the earth, dear master, having endured much toil.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p>Tyrannos, il cane.</p>
                <p>Qui giaccio sotto terra, padrone, dopo tante fatiche.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>الكلب تيرانوس. أنا أرقد هنا تحت الأرض، سيدي العزيز، بعد تحمل الكثير من التعب (أو القيام بالعمل الشاق).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The findspot is situated about 17 km from Cyrene southwards. The dog, who from the image seems to have been a hunting-dog,
                    was probably buried in a country-estate near which his master used to go hunting.</p>
                <p>For dogs' epitaphs, see bibliography at <bibl><ptr target="#chamoux2001"/></bibl> and also <bibl><ptr target="#mendezdosuna2007"/></bibl>.</p>
                <p>Metrical analysis of b): we have here a dactylic heptameter, probably produced by adjunction of <foreign xml:lang="grc">δέσποτα</foreign>
                inside a regular hexameter, with trihemimeric and bucolic caesurae.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
